{
  "stem": "19198.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 198.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were not-- we did not travel by sleeper, and one of the things that impressed us was that to ride in that coach when in the early morning hours a man stood up and put on his tallit and tfillin, and said his morning prayers.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That's something we had never seen in Germany.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we arrived in Cincinnati, where we were met by Dr.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Nelson Glueck, who then was an assistant professor at the Hebrew Union College, and who was given the chore of meeting the students, because he happened to own a station wagon.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The-- at any rate, we got off the train in-- in Cincinnati, thought that somebody might meet us direct-- right at the train.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But nobody seemed to be looking for us, so we were among the last to go from the train into the station.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And a fairly young looking man very reluctantly approached us and in fairly good German asked [SPEAKING GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the reason he was so hesitant-- Translate.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Translate that.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--is that, we found out later, he had gone to another group that had come into the station, and they looked at him.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he then repeated the question in English, and they said, no, we are such and such a band from Brooklyn.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The reason he was doubly hesitant to approach us is that one of the five of us was carrying his precious cello, so he-- he was afraid of musicians.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "At any rate, he introduced himself as-- in good German-- as Dr.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Nelson Gluek and packed us into his station wagon, and took us to-- to his home for breakfast.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "During that breakfast, something interesting happened.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The-- a butler carried a tray.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
